---
description: CSS and Tailwind standards for UI consistency
globs: src/**/*.{tsx,css}
alwaysApply: false
---

- Prefer Tailwind utility classes for component styling; use custom CSS only when utilities are insufficient.
- Keep `src/app/globals.css` minimal (base styles, tokens, and shared primitives only).
- Use mobile-first responsive classes and add breakpoints only when needed.
- Require visible focus states for interactive elements (`focus`/`focus-visible`) and clear disabled/hover states.
- Avoid one-off arbitrary values unless justified by design requirements.
- If the same utility group repeats across multiple components, extract a shared component or helper.
- Keep class lists readable: group related utilities (layout, spacing, typography, state).
- Avoid inline styles unless values must be computed dynamically at runtime.
